Thank you so much!!!! If 188 gets approved to be expanded and we're already on the waitlist, do we have to do anything (i.e. move sections or anything) or do we just get put into the first available section?
Since there is a waitlist, it may only allow you to add to the waitlist and then when the waitlist runs it should move folks into sections and the lecture where space is available.

It looks like the additional 188 section has been approved because there are 40 available seats and the enrollment total is much less than the class capacity. For some reason, the lecture is still waitlisting. Why is this?

Like before, the waitlist goes by lecture position. The first person on the waitlist who can get into the class does so (which means that only people who are waitlisted for a discussion with open room can get in).

I think this explanation is incorrect and here's why (I asked Lily Zhang, a CS advisor, a similar question and she said she wasn't sure. Now I have some proof that it isn't so straightforward). 

Logically, for anybody to enroll in the brand new section for 188, they would have had to drop their current position and re-add the class. CalCentral does not allow you to switch section waitlists if you are in the lecture waitlist, you MUST drop and re-add. Thus, everybody who changed to the new section that was added today would have moved to the end of the lecture waitlist (position 90+). 

A lot of those people did get into the new section, which means that CalCentral definitely moved through the lecture waitlist, moved past me (I was at position 61), and moved onto enrolling those who dropped and re-added the class with the new section. The straightforward answer for why CalCentral did not enroll me, but enrolled those behind me, is that my section was full - but it wasn't.

I had verified with Ms. Zhang merely hours before that my section (115) had 9 spots open and I was 7th on the section waitlist. Given that there is no more EECS priority after phase II, there is no conceivable way that anybody would get ahead of me on the section waitlist - yet section 115 is now filled up and I am still on the lecture waitlist.

In your described method (iterate through the lecture waitlist, check if person's section is full, if full then skip the person, else add the person), there is no way the above scenario could have happened. By the time CalCentral got to me at position 61, section 115 could not have been filled yet based on the number of open seats and my position on the section waitlist. But I was passed over anyways. 

There is no way for me to reconcile what happened with the explanations I've been seeing in this Piazza. I am now 53rd on the lecture waitlist, meaning that a total of only 8 people in front of me dropped and re-enrolled for a new section or got into their original section, meaning that almost everybody out of the 40 newly enrolled people got in from behind me on the lecture waitlist despite a total of about 20 open discussion seats previous to the new section. 

I've resigned myself to sticking with 61C for the semester, but I would love to figure out how this enrollment system actually f-ing works. The explanations on Piazza do not explain my experience, and Ms. Zhang indicated that she too was not sure if things actually worked this way. This has been intensely frustrating and I want to avoid it for future semesters.

history.content:
The College of Engineering provided additional teaching budget yesterday to expand CS classes one final time this semester.

The following classes have already been expanded:

61A : Two more labs added (both in 277 Soda) and enrollment limit expanded by 70:

144C W 9:30-11A

145C W 11A-12:30P

These labs will be in-person labs while the corresponding discussions will be online.

 

161:  Enrollment limit for the lecture was increased to 390. Two more discussion sections added:

    161-111 is now scheduled Wednesdays 5-6P in 320 Soda

    161-112 is now scheduled Wednesdays 6-7P in 320 Soda.

 

162:  Enrollment limit for lecture was increased to 286.  One discussion section added:

         162-112 Th 6:30-7:30P   310 Soda 

///////////////////

We have permission of the Dean to increase the lecture limits and add the following:

170-117: W 2-3P in 310 Soda: you have the room starting on 8/31 (today)
170-118: W 7-8P in 320 Soda: you have the room starting on 9/7 (not tonight but next week)

186-115 Tu 3-4P in 310 Soda

188-108  Tu 2-3P   310  Soda

They are not yet public on the schedule of classes but will be once the scheduling office increases the enrollment limit of the lecture.  I wanted you to have this now so you could begin scheduling the (u)gsis.

The sections are hidden and unavailable for enrollments until campus is able to implement the new enrollment limits for lecture but I thought it might help students to plan if they new about the new section times now.

New capacity in these three classes should be implemented either Wednesday or Thursday this week.  No additional expansion of CS enrollments are expected after this for Fall 2016.
